        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 3 at 6:44AM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 644 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles northeast of Ohio, or 20 miles southwest of Speculator, moving
northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Speculator, Lewey Lake Campground, Moffitt Beach Campground, Perkins
Clearing, Rudeston, West Canada Lakes, Herkimer Landing, Caswell
Lake, Mountain Home, Sled Harbor, Piseco, Morehouseville, and
Hoffmeister.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
